ssible routes from the bookbinder's workshop to their final home in Bristol Central Library. Using multi-spectral imaging to read the damaged sections of text, the authors also provide a full edition of the narrative contained in the fragments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aArthurian.  aBristol Merlin.  aSuite Vulgate du Merlin.  acodicology.  amanuscript fragments.  amanuscript provenance.  apalaeography.1 aChuhan Campbell, Laura, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPohl, Benjamin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRichardson, Michael.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781641894159zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781641894159423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781641894159.jpg  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075412-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBK